'''Film Jam 2025''' was a film jam, hosted in collaboration with the {{Group link|grp_93f6413e-cd62-4c2d-8d2a-62f4adb15b66|Filmmakers of VRChat}} group. It took place from August 4, 2025 - September 1, 2025. Film Jam 2025 was the first jam of its kind, with jams being centred around [[Worlds|worlds]] or [[Avatars|avatars]] previously.

==Details==
===Dates===
Submissions for the jam began on August 4th and closed on September 1st. Submissions were judged from September 2nd to September 12th. The winners of the jam were announced on September 15th, along with their winning films being screened in VRChat hosted by the {{Group link|grp_93f6413e-cd62-4c2d-8d2a-62f4adb15b66|Filmmakers of VRChat}} group.

===Theme===
Participants of the jam could pick between 3 themes:<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/film-jam-2025-august-4-september-1-2025/45595 Film Jam 2025 - August 4 - September 1 2025]</ref>

* The One Who Changed It All
* Two Days, One Moment
* Not Doomed Yet

Submissions were judged in the following categories:
* Story & Concept (Originality, narrative structure, theme, emotional impact, clarity of message)
* Direction & Execution (Overall vision, shot composition, pacing, tone, performances, and how well all parts come together)
* Technical Craft (Cinematography, editing, sound design, music, visual effects, animation, lighting)
* Art & Style (Visual creativity, World choices, Avatar Choices, color grading, and artistic choices)

====Requirements====
In addition to the general theme, submissions needed to follow these requirements:
* Film must be made specifically for this Jam.
* Film must be between 1-10 minutes long
* Film must have EN subtitles baked into the film.
* Film must be PG-13 content rating.

To see the full list of requirements, see [https://ask.vrchat.com/t/film-jam-2025-august-4-september-1-2025/45595#p-82914-some-additional-requirements-4 here] and [https://hello.vrchat.com/film-jam-2025-official-rules here].

===Prizes===
[[File:FilmJam2025Badge.png|thumb|120x120px|The "Film Jam (2025)" badge.]]
The teams of the top 10 winners of the jam were awarded the following:
* 1 year of [[VRC+]] (spilt up between a max of 12 team members)
* An exclusive [[Badges|badge]] (limited to 12 team members)
* Opportunity to be showcased in a public playlist on the official VRChat YouTube account
* Opportunity to be screened during the September 19 Premiere

